{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Operations Flow{% endblock %}

{% block pageContent %}
<div class="min-h-[80vh] overflow-hidden">
    <div class="relative isolate overflow-hidden rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 via-emerald-900/30 to-cyan-800/20 p-10 shadow-xl mb-10">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-30" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="absolute -left-10 -top-10 h-64 w-64 rounded-full bg-cyan-500 blur-3xl"></div>
            <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 h-72 w-72 rounded-full bg-indigo-500 blur-3xl"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="relative space-y-4 max-w-4xl">
            <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-cyan-200/80 flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="size-5 opacity-80">
                    <path d="M3 12h18"></path>
                    <path d="M8 7l-2 5 2 5"></path>
                    <path d="M16 7l2 5-2 5"></path>
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"></circle>
                </svg>
                Operations Flow
            </p>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight">Operational dossier: from campaign clock to signed credits.</h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-200/90">
                This briefing lays out the full administrative flow: Campaign, Company, Crew, Ship, Mortgage, Income, Cost, Annual Budget and the rules that keep them coherent across session time and contracts.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-200/70">
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Cross-campaign Companies</span>
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Imperial Dates</span>
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Crew Status Timeline</span>
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Mortgage Signature</span>
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Contract PDFs</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-cyan-200 mb-3">
                {% include 'icons/alien-structure-1.html.twig' %}
                <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em]">Campaign Directive</p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Campaign</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">
                The campaign is the master clock. Set starting year and session date (day/year) and keep it updated as in‑game time advances. Every downstream date, limit, and PDF reads from this clock.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                <li>Session date drives form limits and PDF “generated on” stamps.</li>
                <li>Ships inherit the campaign calendar for all day/year fields.</li>
                <li>Campaign is the anchor for costs, income, and mortgage signatures.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-cyan-200 mb-3">
                {% include 'icons/company.html.twig' %}
                <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em]">Counterparty Registry</p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Company</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">
                Companies are cross‑campaign entities. Register them once with roles, contact data, and LocalLaw; reuse them in any campaign without duplicating legal metadata.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                <li>LocalLaw data flows into Cost/Income/Mortgage PDFs.</li>
                <li>Company roles clarify counterparties across all contracts.</li>
                <li>Cross‑campaign reuse keeps signatures consistent.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-cyan-200 mb-3">
                {% include 'icons/crew.html.twig' %}
                <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em]">Roster Protocol</p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Crew</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">
                Crew status is a timeline. When assigned from the unassigned roster, the crew member is set to Active and stamped with the session date.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                <li>Statuses: Active, On Leave, Retired, Missing (MIA), Deceased.</li>
                <li>Unassigned lists exclude Missing/Deceased by default.</li>
                <li>Detaching a crew from ship clears Active/On Leave/Retired dates and status (except MIA/Deceased).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-cyan-200 mb-3">
                {% include 'icons/far-trader.html.twig' %}
                <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em]">Hull Manifest</p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Ship</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">
                Ships are the core asset. Each hull has a single mortgage, a crew roster, and a detailed ship sheet (JSON components) for PDF printing.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                <li>Ship details track drives, systems, and total component cost.</li>
                <li>Campaign association synchronizes all day/year fields.</li>
                <li>Crew assignments and roles are managed per ship.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-cyan-200 mb-3">
                {% include 'icons/handbook.html.twig' %}
                <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em]">Lien File</p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Mortgage</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">
                Mortgages are signed using the campaign session date and a recorded signing location. A signed mortgage can be printed as an official record or kept as a draft.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                <li>Signing stamps day/year + location and locks PDF metadata.</li>
                <li>Crew panels in UI/PDF only show Active crew on or after the signing date.</li>
                <li>Installments follow the Traveller 13‑period year.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-cyan-200 mb-3">
                {% include 'icons/income.html.twig' %}
                <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em]">Revenue Docket</p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Income</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">
                Income is typed by category, each with its own detail sheet. Contract PDFs are generated with LocalLaw and company data for on‑table signatures.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                <li>Imperial dates are shown as DDD/YYYY with optional clear.</li>
                <li>Category‑specific details are enforced by dynamic forms.</li>
                <li>Contract PDFs mirror the data structure for auditing.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-cyan-200 mb-3">
                {% include 'icons/cost.html.twig' %}
                <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em]">Expense Ledger</p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Cost</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">
                Costs are logged per ship with detailed line items. LocalLaw and counterparties are printed in PDF for jurisdictional clarity.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                <li>Detail items feed the computed amount field.</li>
                <li>Payment dates use imperial day/year.</li>
                <li>PDF formatting stays consistent across contracts.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-cyan-200 mb-3">
                {% include 'icons/annual-budget.html.twig' %}
                <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em]">Balance Strip</p>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Annual Budget</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">
                Annual Budget is the ship’s fiscal strip for the session year: it aggregates Income, Cost, and mortgage installments into a single operational readout.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                <li>One budget per ship, tied to imperial start/end day/year.</li>
                <li>Timeline blends payouts, upkeep, and debt across 13 periods.</li>
                <li>Use it to forecast solvency before the next jump.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
